# 四、Band 8 改写版（建议精读）

The bar chart illustrates the results of a survey on coffee and tea consumption habits in five Australian cities over the previous four weeks.

Overall, visiting cafés for coffee or tea was the most popular activity in most cities, particularly in Melbourne and Hobart. By contrast, purchasing fresh coffee tended to be the least common habit overall. In addition, residents in Brisbane and Hobart showed relatively strong preferences for instant coffee.

Approximately 64% of residents in Melbourne had visited a café during the previous four weeks, representing the highest proportion among the five cities. Hobart followed closely at around 63%, while the figures for Sydney and Brisbane were slightly lower, at roughly 61% and 55% respectively. Adelaide recorded the lowest percentage of café visits, at just under 50%.

Regarding coffee purchases, instant coffee was more popular than fresh coffee in every city. Around 54% of residents in Hobart bought instant coffee, compared with approximately 53% in Brisbane and 50% in Adelaide. The figures for Melbourne and Sydney were lower, at about 48% and 45% respectively. By comparison, fresh coffee purchases were highest in Sydney, at around 44%, whereas Brisbane and Adelaide recorded the lowest proportions, both at approximately 34%.

